testbed.gui.gmi
Class InterfaceData

java.lang.Object
  testbed.gui.gmi.InterfaceData

public class InterfaceData
extends java.lang.Object

This class holds all data required to update a GameMonitorInterface for a single timestep.

Author:
K. Fullam

InterfaceData

public InterfaceData(int _timestep,
                     java.util.Hashtable _bankBalances,
                     java.util.Hashtable _transFees,
                     java.util.Hashtable _weights,
                     java.util.Hashtable _appErrAvgs,
                     java.util.Hashtable _appErrStDevs,
                     java.util.Hashtable _cerTransactions,
                     java.util.Hashtable _opTransactions,
                     java.util.Hashtable _repTransactions,
                     java.util.Vector _systemMessages,
                     java.util.Hashtable _clients,
                     java.util.Hashtable _messageCounts)
Creates a new instance of InterfaceData. This constructor would generally be called by the DataBase module to fill an InterfaceData for sending to the GameMonitorInterface.

Parameters:
_timestep - Timestep (int) during which data is collected.
_bankBalances - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of agent bank balances (doubles) during this timestep.
_transFees - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of Hashtables. Inner Hashtables are keyed by transaction fee type and contain net transaction fees paid to/by this agent during this timestep.
_weights - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of Hashtables, keyed by agent weights are about, of Hashtables, keyed by eraName, of weights.
_appErrAvgs - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of agent appraisal error averages (doubles) during this timestep.
_appErrStDevs - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of agent appraisal error standard deviations (doubles) during this timestep.
_cerTransactions - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of Hashtables. Inner Hashtables contain a "To" key and "From" key for each other agent in the system. Each element contains the number of certainties sent "To" or "From" the other agent in this timestep.--this is WRONG! Let inner hashtables hold a single row (for row "From agent X", all of the "To" values). Let outer hashtables hold all of the rows
_opTransactions - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of Hashtables. Inner Hashtables contain a "To" key and "From" key for each other agent in the system. Each element contains the number of opinions sent "To" or "From" the other agent in this timestep.--this is WRONG! Let inner hashtables hold a single row (for row "From agent X", all of the "To" values). Let outer hashtables hold all of the rows
_repTransactions - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of Hashtables. Inner Hashtables contain a "To" key and "From" key for each other agent in the system. Each element contains the number of reputations sent "To" or "From" the other agent in this timestep.--this is WRONG! Let inner hashtables hold a single row (for row "From agent X", all of the "To" values). Let outer hashtables hold all of the rows
_systemMessages - A Vector of all Messages between all pairs of agents in this timestep.
_clients - A Hashtable, keyed by agent name, of (doubles) clients held by each agent during this timestep.
_messageCounts - A Hashtable, keyed by message type, of Hashtables, keyed by sending agent, of Hashtables, keyed by receiving agent, of number of messages (ints).
